    {
      "title": "2022 ACCOMPLISHMENTS",
      "elements": [
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Awarded $272 million in GREAT grants with $147 million match to expand high-speed internet access to 109,988 households and 3,626 businesses in rural communities",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            }
          ],
          "lang": null,
          "readingOrder": null
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Awarded $24 million in state’s first Digital Equity Grant program to expand digital literacy training, device access and digital inclusion planning",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            }
          ],
          "lang": null,
          "readingOrder": null
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Supported 24 state and local government and academic institutions, with remediation and recovery from ransomware/cyber events",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            }
          ],
          "lang": null,
          "readingOrder": null
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Created a Privacy and Data Protection website, established monthly meetings and provided privacy guidance and consultation to 11+ state agencies",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            }
          ],
          "lang": null,
          "readingOrder": null
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Migrated 126 public safety answering points and 193 physical locations to the Emergency Services Protocol Network, which supports Next Generation 911",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            }
          ],
          "lang": null,
          "readingOrder": null
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Established the Longitudinal Data System Governance Board to provide guidance and support to NCDIT’s Government Data Analytics Center in developing the Educational Longitudinal Data System",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            }
          ],
          "lang": null,
          "readingOrder": null
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Expanded the fraud framework for the N.C. Division of Employment Security and implemented a new alert system for suspicious registered claimants to proactively identify and stop payments of potentially fraudulent unemployment benefits, resulting in the discovery of 1,884 confirmed cases of identity theft",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            }
          ],
          "lang": null,
          "readingOrder": null
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Expanded the N.C. Department of Revenue's analytic footprint to support detection of fraud of tax compliance, resulting in an efficiency gain of $5.3 million annually and an additional $16.4 million in audit assessments",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            }
          ],
          "lang": null,
          "readingOrder": null
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Developed, with the assistance of a grant, a stroke registry in partnership with the N.C. Division of Public Health and the Justice-Warren Heart Disease and Stroke Prevention Task Force to enhance the stroke system of care statewide",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            }
          ],
          "lang": null,
          "readingOrder": null
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Provided the N.C. Office of State Human Resources and Cabinet agencies with a secure online reporting tool and new dashboard to meet the Covid-19 vaccine monitoring and testing requirements for state employees",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            }
          ],
          "lang": null,
          "readingOrder": null
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Launched a new version of ",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            },
            {
              "href": "https://NC.gov",
              "text": "NC.gov",
              "title": null,
              "opensNewWindow": true
            },
            {
              "text": " as a constituent portal to make it easier for users to find and utilize all state services, including an improved search function and better customer service",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            }
          ],
          "lang": null,
          "readingOrder": null
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Enrolled more than 650,000 residents in the FCC’s Affordable Connectivity Plan that provides subsidies for high-speed internet service and the one-time purchase of a computer",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            }
          ],
          "lang": null,
          "readingOrder": null
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Updated the N.C. Identification Management (NCID) service to a modern cloud-based service, enhancing security and improving self-service of the project",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            }
          ],
          "lang": null,
          "readingOrder": null
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Implemented AddressNC, demonstrating the partnership between NCDIT’s Geographic Information Systems technology unit and local governments to bring map data together for an enterprise use and to improve services",
              "bold": false,
              "italic": false,
              "underline": false,
              "strikethrough": false,
              "superscript": false,
              "subscript": false,
              "code": false,
              "lang": null
            }
          ],
          "lang": null,
          "readingOrder": null
        }
      ],
